@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Arroze' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  Clicking on an arrow (one of the angular shapes) will make it
rotate 90 degres clockwise, unless that arrow is immediately next
to and points towards the empty space. In that case, the arrow will
move to the position occupied by the empty space.

  What complicates matters a little, is that every time you move or
rotate an arrow, and the empty space is not placed at the ending
position, one arrow -maybe the one you already clicked on- will
randomly rotate...

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

@endnode

